<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" standalone="no"?> 
<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../man.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>zeropen  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="zeropen"> zero pencil  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[Z,U]=zeropen(Sl)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>Sl  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : a linear system (<VERB>syslin</VERB> list in state-space form <VERB>[A,B,C,D]</VERB>)
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>Z  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : matrix pencil <VERB>Z=s*E-A</VERB>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>U  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : square orthogonal matrix
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    <VERB>Z = sE - F</VERB>  is the zero pencil of the linear system <VERB>Sl</VERB> with 
    matrices <VERB>[A,B,C,D]</VERB>. Utility function.
  </P>
  <P>
    With <VERB>U</VERB> row compression of <VERB>[B;D]</VERB> i.e, <VERB>U*[B;D]=[0;*]</VERB>; one has:
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
U*[-sI+A |B;   [ Z |0;      
      C  |D] = [ * |*]
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    The zeros of <VERB>Z</VERB> are the zeros of <VERB>Sl</VERB>.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <SEE_ALSO>
    <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>systmat</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>     <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>kroneck</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>
  </SEE_ALSO>
</MAN>
